We are given a linkedlist as input and left and right we have to reverse the nodes that are between left and right. 

Solution Approach:

First we take a dummy node and interate until left ( i = 0 to left -1 )
Then we use Reverse linked list technique to reverse elements in the list from left  to right - left + 1
Then once reverse is done we merge it with the original sequence.
Now we return the dummy.next.



class Solution {
    public ListNode reverseBetween(ListNode head, int left, int right) {


        ListNode dummy = new ListNode(0);

        dummy.next = head;

        ListNode beforeSublist = dummy;

        for(int i = 0; i < left - 1 ; i++)
        {
            beforeSublist = beforeSublist.next;
        }


        
        ListNode curr = beforeSublist.next;
        ListNode prev = null;

        for(int i =0; i < right - left + 1; i++)
        {
            ListNode temp = curr.next;
            curr.next = prev;
            prev = curr;
            curr = temp;
        }

        beforeSublist.next.next = curr;
        beforeSublist.next = prev;

        return dummy.next;


    }
}
